OL,6,GThe National Union of Journalists says
OL,7,Git will ballot members for industrial
OL,8,Gaction following a decision by BBC
OL,9,Gmanagement to abandon talks and press
OL,10,Gahead with changes to the BBC Radio
OL,11,GFoyle schedule.
OL,13,FLast November, the BBC announced plans
OL,14,Fto axe the weekday Breakfast Show on
OL,15,FBBC Radio Foyle, as well as hourly news
OL,16,Fbulletins and the 30-minute lunchtime
OL,17,Fnews programme. Eight journalist
OL,18,Fpositions were to be removed from the
OL,19,Fstation.
OL,21,FEarlier today, revised proposals were
OL,22,Fmade public:
OL,3,CNUJ to ballot members for industrial
OL,4,Caction over Foyle changes
