PN,35002
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F350A1679356768
OL,6,
OL,7,F The Breakfast Show is to continue,
OL,8,Fbut reduced from 2 hours to 30 minutes.
OL,9,F Hourly news bulletins are to be
OL,10,Fretained.
OL,11,F The lunchtime news programme will
OL,12,Fstill be axed.
OL,13,F The BBC says it expects staffing
OL,14,Flevels to remain unchanged: "This
OL,15,Fincludes some new roles to help deliver
OL,16,Flocal and region-wide programming
OL,17,Facross the BBC's services."
OL,18,F Production of some BBC Radio Ulster
OL,19,Fprogrammes would move to BBC Radio
OL,20,FFoyle (the Hugo Duncan afternoon show
OL,21,Fand evening programmes, including those
OL,22,Fpresented by Ralph McLean and Eve
OL,23,FBlair).
OL,3,CNUJ to ballot members for industrial
OL,4,Caction over Foyle changes
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
